Having considered the General Assembly
resolution of 2 December 1950 (document A/1616) on the subject
of the Ewe problem;

Considering that these methods
represented an effort to enable the sections of the population
concerned to express their opinions;

Hawing considered the General Assembly
resolution of 2 December 1950 (A/1616) on the subject of the Ewe
problem;

Considering that these methods were such
as to enable all sections of the population to express their
true opinions;
